– Painted green, hit by green: target is made invisible for one round and takes 5 Poison damage per second for one round as well
– Painted green, hit by red: target is cursed as by the Contagion spell, but as a semi-permanent curse with a -4 save vs. breath
– Painted green, hit by blue: target is Hasted, but suffers from a -10 penalty to melee damage
– Painted red, hit by red: target immediately takes 4d6 slashing damage
– Painted red, hit by green: target must save vs. death or be knocked unconscious for one round
– Painted red, hit by blue: all nearby enemies and allies receive 50% resistance from electricity
– Painted blue, hit by blue: target is given two extra attacks per round but cannot cast spells for 3 seconds
– Painted blue, hit by red: target is struck by lightning and takes 7d7 lightning damage
– Painted blue, hit by green: target takes 2d4 cold damage and is slowed for 1 round
– For the specific combination of Red to Green to Blue, all previous effects are to be negated and a Rogue Stone is created in the target's inventory

