@1046 = ~Vampiric Dart of Eternal Hunger~
@1047 = ~Once held by the notorious necromancer Szass Tam, the lich lord of Thay, the Vampiric Dart of Eternal Hunger embodies the perpetual craving of the undead. Forged through a gruesome ritual involving the sacrificial blood of a hundred innocents from the realm of Aglarond, the dart is a vessel of insatiable thirst. When held, it feels unnaturally cold, and a faint pulse can be sensed, mirroring a heartbeat that no longer exists.

Its thirst for life is particularly potent against the pure-hearted, drawing greater sustenance from their virtuous souls. The dart's hunger extends to magic itself, occasionally reigniting the fading embers of the wielder's own spells. However, the wielder must be cautious, for the dart demands a price, sipping away a fragment of their vitality upon being equipped.

